WHO   — STRIFE — a polemos sphere — conflict & strategy
WHAT  — Before any particular war there is strife itself — the principle of conflict. The Greeks gave it a goddess, Eris, whose golden apple 'to the fairest' set gods against one another and lit the Trojan War. And the philosopher Heraclitus made the darker claim that strife is not a flaw in the world but its engine: 'war is the father of all,' the tension that holds everything in form.
WHERE — the field of conflict — from the dawn of writing  Framework inputs: strife; the word; the might; the idea  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
